        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>[In Chri]sti nomine. Anni ab incarnacione eiusdem millesimo CLVI, tempore
                            <persName key="#Popes" ref="#people/4312">ADRiani</persName> pape et
                            <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/124">Federici</persName>
                        imperatoris, [die secun]do intrante mense aprelis, indic(ione) quarta, sub
                        portico <orgName key="#Churches">Sancte Agnetis</orgName>
                        <placeName ref="#places/80">Ferrarie</placeName>. Venerabilium quidem
                        locorum res quidem [ill]e que <rs key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis">iure
                            enphyteotico</rs> plerumque traduntur nisi tueantur et ab ipsis
                        petitoribus meliorentur [non] aliter a sacris permittitur constitutionibus.
                        Omnibus manifestum est quapropter vos domnus <persName key="#Abbots"
                            ref="#people/4310">Iohannes</persName> gratia Dei humilis <rs
                            key="#Abbots">abbas</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Rivers #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Fundi #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Rent_in_money #Canals #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio #Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/1460">Sancte Marie de
                                <placeName ref="#places/4179">Pomposea</placeName></orgName>,
                        consenciente cuncto conventu eiusdem monasterii, ab [a]c die per hanc
                        enphyteosin paginam concedistis nobis rem quam per anteriorem enphyteosin
                        paginam [h]abuimus et tenuimus a iure predicti monasterii, michi presenti
                                <persName><name ref="Wido de Sabluncello">Guidoni de
                                Sabluncello</name></persName>, pro me et pro <persName><name
                                ref="Tabaria">Tabaria</name></persName> et <persName><name
                                ref="Pretiosa">Persiuse</name></persName> germane meę, de hoc quod
                        nobis pertinet per anteriorem enphyteosin ex parte patris nostri et quantum
                            <rs key="#Venditio">emi</rs> a quondam <persName>
                            <name ref="Albertus">Alberto</name></persName> et Gunti[..]la in una
                        parte et mihi <persName><name ref="Tauruncellus"
                            >Taruncello</name></persName>, pro me et pro <persName><name
                                ref="Ingeltruda">Engeltruda</name></persName> et <persName><name
                                ref="Egina">Egina</name></persName> et <persName><name ref="Tarduza"
                                >Tarduza</name></persName> et <persName><name ref="Nabilia"
                                >Nabilia</name></persName> germane meę et pro <persName><name
                                ref="Richilda">Richelda</name></persName> et filia <persName><name
                                ref="Claretia">Clarce</name></persName> consobrine meę, si voluerint
                        persolvere precium in alia parte, seu filiis et nepotibus nostris − filios
                        autem et nepotes si non habuerimus liceat unicuique nostrum ordinare duos
                        successores unum post alterum mediocris persone libere qui post nostrum
                        decessum habeant − res inferius dicendas, si iuste tamen et racionabiliter
                        petivimus vel ab aliis minime detinere videtur, idest de <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">LXV masariciis</rs> concedis nobis per
                        enphyteoticarium ius tres masaricias et terciam partem unius masaricie sitas
                        in <rs key="#Fundi">fundo</rs>
                        <geogName
                            key="#Rivers #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Fundi #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Rent_in_money #Canals #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio"
                            ref="#estates/2470">
                            <placeName key="#Rivers #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Fundi #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Rent_in_money #Canals #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio" ref="#places/4699">Puvignani</placeName></geogName> et
                        territorio infra hec <rs key="#Confinia">latera</rs>: primo latere <rs
                            key="#Canals">canalis</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Confinia #Canals" ref="#places/4858">Fussco</placeName>, secundo latere <rs
                            key="#Canals">Fossa</rs> de <placeName key="#Confinia #Canals"><geogName
                                key="#Confinia #Canals" ref="#estates/2471"
                            >Gardilana</geogName></placeName>, tercio latere <placeName
                            key="#Confinia"><geogName key="#Confinia" ref="#estates/2471"
                                >Gardillana</geogName></placeName>, quarto latere <placeName
                            key="#Confinia" ref="#places/3544">Arcuada</placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Confinia #Rivers" ref="#places/4856"><rs key="#Rivers">Gurgo</rs>
                            Fossaltule</placeName> et <placeName key="#Confinia #Canals" ref="#places/4857">Fossato
                            Novo</placeName> et paino <placeName key="#Confinia" ref="#places/4855"
                            >Fraxiniane</placeName>. Que omnia cum <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >terris</rs>, <rs key="#Rivers">aquis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">paludibus</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">vallibus</rs>, <rs key="#Canals"
                            >canalibus</rs>, <rs key="#Fisheries">pisscationibus</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">capellacionibus</rs> et
                        cum omnibus ad prescriptis rebus pertinentibus, cum introitu et exitu earum
                        et cum omnibus suis iustis et certis fini[bus]. Unde quia exinde accepistis
                        a nobis, calciarii nomine, libras tres et solidos XIII et denarii quaptuor
                        denariorum Lucensium. Dedistis nobis investitorem <persName key="#Missus"
                                ><name ref="Alexandrinus">Alexandrinum</name></persName> vestrum <rs
                            key="#Missus">missum</rs> qui nos in prescriptis rebus corporaliter
                        investiat. Dum nos superius nominatis petitoribus enphyteoticariis atque
                        filiis et nepotibus nostris, secundum quod inter nos iuste dividere debemus,
                        divina gratia in ac luce iusserit permanere vitam, concedistis predictas res
                        habendas, tenendas, fruendas, defensandas et meliorandas et annualem
                        pensionem vestre dominationi omni mense marcio <rs key="#Rent_in_money"
                            >denarios duo V(e)r(on)en(ses)</rs> persolvendum. Nec liceat nobis neque
                        nostris filiis et nepotibus de prescriptis rebus ad aliud <rs
                            key="#Districtio">placitum</rs> ire nisi ante vos vestrosque successores
                        neque alienare nisi inter fratres et consortes neque in alico venerabili
                        loco relinquere. Que omnia ut super legitur observare et adimplere
                        promittimus n[os] nostrosque heredes vobis vestrisque successoribus, sub
                        pena <rs key="#Penalty">trium unciarum auri</rs> et soluta pena maneat firma
                        hec enphyteosin pagina. Quam scribere rogavimus <persName key="#Notary"
                                ><name ref="Petrus Bonus">Petrum Bonum</name></persName> Dei nutu
                            <rs key="#Notary">notarium</rs> de <rs key="#Vici">vico</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Vici" ref="#places/4696">Baurie</placeName> et manibus
                        nostris firmavimus, in die et indic(ione) prescripta. Ad hec fuerunt testes:
                        presbiter Dominicus, Rodulfus iudex, Donodeus, Bonus Iohannes iudex filius
                        eius, Ugo de Bonafante, Petricinus, Petrus Bonus, Lanfrancus, Berardus et
                        Alexandrinus investitor. EGO PETRUS Bonus Dei nutu Pomposianus notarius, ita
                        ut rogatus fui, scripsi.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
